Governor Henry Seriake Dickson of Bayelsa State has signed the Community Safety Corps Amendment Bill 2018. The Special Adviser to the Governor on Public Affairs, Daniel Alabrah, in a statement yesterday, quoted Dickson as saying the new law would enable security agencies to carry out their operations more effectively in the state. The governor pledged his continued support to the security agencies in the state to guarantee the safety of all section of the state and its citizens. The speaker of the House of Assembly, Konbowei Benson, said the amended law was an embodiment of all security related laws passed by the state legislature. Taraba gov signs anti-grazing law Stop politicising security in Bayelsa â€“ APC tells PDP, Dickson Dickson signs medical university bill, two others